  <source>Groupe Hospitalier Pitie-Salpetriere</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bilateral pallidal stimulation is effective in the treatment of patients with generalised
      idiopathic dystonia. The aim of this study is to evaluate the efficacy of bilateral pallidal
      stimulation in patients with post-anoxic generalised dystonia or non-generalised primary
      dystonia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Evaluate the effect of bilateral pallidal stimulation on the motor disability of patients
      with post-anoxic generalised dystonia or primary dystonia.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
